<TITLE> All colleges reopen Saturday, most universities soon </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 7 (bdnews24.com) - All public and private colleges in the divisional headquarters and in districts resume classes Saturday. The Bangladesh University of Engineering and Technology (BUET), Shahjalal University of Science and Technology (SUST) and Patuakhali University of Engineering and Technology (KUET) reopen Monday. The residential halls of the Noakhali University of Science and Technology (NUST) reopened Friday and the classes resume Saturday. Khulna University of Engineering and Technology (KUET) reopens Sunday. The dormitories of Dhaka Sher-e-Bangla Agricultural University will reopen on September 12. The Rajshahi University vice-chancellor said they expected to take the tests, if not restart classes, in Ramadan. The Rajshahi University of Engineering and Technology (RUET) is scheduled to resume classes after Ramadan. Authorities decided in a meeting Thursday to reopen Chittagong University on Oct 24. The syndicates of Dhaka University, Jahangirnagar University and Mymensingh Agricultural University will meet Saturday to set the date for reopening. The syndicate meeting of Jagannath University will be held Sunday noon. On Aug 23, the government closed 26 universities and dormitories and all colleges in divisional headquarters in the wake of the bloodiest campus violence that erupted at Dhaka University on Aug 20. The decision to resume universities came from a Sep 3 meeting between the vice-chancellors and education adviser Aiyub Quadri. Prof Abul Khaer, the NUST vice-chancellor, told bdnews24.com two dormitories of the university reopened Friday. Prof Khaer said the situation at the university was normal and the classes would resume Saturday. SUST would resume classes Monday. Shah Paran and other two male and female students' halls will reopen Saturday. Dr Aminul Islam, vice-chancellor of the university, said to bdnews24.com,"I hope the classes will resume amid a normal situation." But panic gripped the students as the police filed a case Thursday with Kotwali Police Station against 30 people including Mostafizur Rahman, organising secretary of Bangladesh Chhatra League, the student wing of the Awami League. Sylhet Agricultural University will resume classes Monday and the dormitories will open Sunday, vice-chancellor Iqbal Hossain said. "The situation in the university is normal. I expect help from others as it is a new university," Hossain said. The university started academic activities this year. Rajshahi University vice-chancellor Prof M Altaf Hossain said he expected the university would reopen in Ramadan. He said he was going to Dhaka to discuss the re-opening the university and the current situation with the education ministry. The syndicate would take a decision in this regard in a meeting. Prof Altaf said they were trying to contact the ministry over resumption of classes. The situation at his university was different than it was in other universities as eight teachers of the university were in jail, he said. The vice-chancellor said the procedure for admission test would be complete in Ramadan after discussion with the admission test committee. The syndicate of Poet Qazi Nazrul Islam University in Mymensingh will meet on Sep 12 to decide when the university would reopen, vice-chancellor Dr M Shamsur Rahman told bdnews24.com. bdnews24
